  "culturalTip": "When you visit a pharmacy in Korea to have a prescription filled, you may receive small packets of medicine that are already separated into individual doses. However, there are usually no instructions on the packets, so you will have to speak with the pharmacist who will be more familiar with the doctor's prescription. People in Korea tend to visit the pharmacy closest to the doctor's office or hospital to fill their prescription. If you need an English-speaking pharmacist, then you can go to that pharmacy to have it filled.",
